      "@id": "https://ssbd.riken.jp/v2/project/299-Satoh-Endosome",
      "@type": "Dataset",
      "identifier": "299-Satoh-Endosome",
      "name": "Endosome maturation promoted by interorganelle association between mitochondria and endosomes",
      "description": "Intracellular organelles of mammalian cells communicate with one another during various cellular processes. The functions and molecular mechanisms of such interorganelle association remain largely unclear, however. The authors identify voltage-dependent anion channel 2 (VDAC2), a mitochondrial outer membrane protein, as a binding partner of phosphoinositide 3-kinase (PI3K), a regulator of clathrin-independent endocytosis downstream of the small GTPase Ras. VDAC2 tethers endosomes positive for the Ras-PI3K complex to mitochondria in response to cell stimulation with epidermal growth factor and promotes clathrin-independent endocytosis, as well as endosome maturation at membrane association sites. With an optogenetics system to induce mitochondrion-endosome association, the authors find that, in addition to its structural role in such association, VDAC2 is functionally implicated in the promotion of endosome maturation.",
      "datePublished": "2024-12-14",
